description: Back-formation from jaywalker. Analyzable as jay (“a stupid person”)+walk

verbs.description: jaywalk (third-person singular simple present jaywalks, present participle jaywalking, simple past and past participle jaywalked)

entries.meaning: (chiefly US, law) To behave as a jaywalker; to violate pedestrian traffic regulations by crossing a street away from a designated crossing or to walk in the part of the street intended for vehicles rather than on the sidewalk.
